title: Boys Golf Roundup: Division III Sectional
text:
Boys Golf Roundup: Division III Sectional Telegraph-Forum staff report 9:25 p.m. EDT October 1, 2015 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Division III Sectional 
Top three teams and top three individuals not on a qualifying team advance. Ottawa Hills placed first with 317, St. Mary Central Catholic was second with 330 and Stritch Catholic was third with 337. Christian Smith of St. Joseph Central Catholic, Austin Berkel and Mitchell Miller of Woodmore advance to districts. 
Colonel Crawford placed 11th out of 14 teams with a score of 401. Nick Gremling (94), Isaak Sulser (96), Eli Shultz (105), and Austin Strouse (106). 
Crestline placed 12th out of 14 teams with a scores of 456. Zac Hatfield (105), Max Anatra (113), Gabe Lutz (117) and Ethan Tharp (121). 
Edison Invitational 
Bucyrus did not score in the Edison Invitational but were led by Keegan Sims with a 85, Keith Smith with a 106 and Dakota Picou with a score of 130. Ashland won the event with a overall score of 307 Read or Share this story: http://ohne.ws/1FJOz7P TOP VIDEOS
